    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-03T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="418"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">888.2553/2–354: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 418<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom (<persName
                            corresp="#p_AWW1" type="from">Aldrich</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d418fn1">Repeated to Tehran.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-03T19:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 3, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3314. Limit distribution. From <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName>. At
                    several small meetings this week involving <persName corresp="#p_CSHA1">Sir
                        Harold Caccia</persName> (replacing <persName corresp="#p_DSP1">Sir Pierson
                        Dixon</persName> at Foreign Office effective February 1) and/or <persName
                        corresp="#p_MSJRP1">Maud</persName> of Ministry Fuel and Power on <gloss
                        target="#t_HMG1">HMG</gloss> side, and <persName corresp="#p_BWW1"
                        >Butterworth</persName> and/or <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName>
                    on US side, present situation appears following: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Official attitude <gloss target="#t_HMG1">HMG</gloss> and <gloss
                                target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> continues that (a) <gloss
                                target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> should have minimum 50 per cent
                            participation in consortium with tacit assumption of dominance in
                            management, and (b) that consortium negotiating team headed by <gloss
                                target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> should go Tehran in approximately one
                            month to start final negotiations with Iran Government determine
                            simultaneously (1) maximum participation <gloss target="#t_AIOC1"
                                >AIOC</gloss> may obtain and (2) other remaining terms of
                            agreement.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Some encouraging indications that <gloss target="#t_HMG1">HMG</gloss>
                            considering modification above attitude, but action by no means certain
                            since such change would require Cabinet decision.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_CSHA1">Caccia</persName> and <persName
                                corresp="#p_MSJRP1">Maud</persName> appeared attach considerable
                            significance our statements that US Government did not desire (a) to
                            reduce participation of <gloss target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> for
                            purpose of obtaining greater share for US <pb facs="0944" n="918"
                                xml:id="pg_918"/> companies and (b) that US companies should have
                            larger share than <gloss target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss>.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>I considering return Washington next few days, unless advised
                            contrary, for purpose discussion US position and future policies with
                            Department and heads US companies.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Aldrich</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
